# Game Design Document â€” Core Systems

## Player Agency
Primary interactions:
- Decision-making during flight (skill usage)
- Resource management
- Pre-launch setup optimization

## Heroes
MVP:
- 1 hero (scalable to 4)
- Stats-based differentiation

Hero Properties:
- Force
- Weight
- Intelligence
- Skill Charges

Hero Abilities:
- 2 Active Skills
- 1 Passive Skill
- Skills may use:
  - Cooldowns
  - Per-flight limits
  - Hybrid systems

## Intelligence Stat
Affects:
- Timing window forgiveness
- Angle tolerance during launch

## Launchers
- 3 launchers + 1 launched hero (future scaling)
- Launcher passives influence:
  - Launch force
  - Modifiers

## Launch Input
Hybrid system:
- Angle selection
- Power modifiers
- Timing click
- Modulated by hero stats and items

## Flight Phase
- Side-scroll style
- Active skills usable
- Resource recovery possible mid-flight
- Camera remains stable (no dynamic tracking in MVP)

## Board Map
- 40 tiles per map
- Fog of War applies to tile effects, not distance
- Overlay minimap visible during flight

Tile Types:
- Neutral
- Event (one-time)
- Modifier (run-altering)
- Vendor
- Checkpoint

## Economy
- Currency earned per flight/run
- Vendors appear only on tiles
- Items are unidentified until purchased
- One backpack slot per hero

## Bosses (Post-MVP Concept)
Bosses are system challenges, not enemies:
- Economy stress tests
- Skill restriction runs
- Launcher debuff challenges

## MVP Scope
Included:
- 1 map
- 1 hero
- Basic launch loop
- Neutral tiles
- Vendor with basic items

Excluded:
- Lore
- Bosses
- Multiplayer

